	shorttitle = {The {PROMIS}® Smoking Initiative},
	abstract = {Introduction: The Patient-Reported Outcomes Measurement Information System ({PROMIS}®) Smoking Initiative has developed 6 item banks for assessing smoking behaviors and biopsychosocial correlates of smoking among daily and nondaily adult cigarette smokers. This paper presents descriptive information and preliminary validity evidence for the item banks (Nicotine Dependence, Coping Expectancies, Emotional and Sensory Expectancies, Health Expectancies, Psychosocial Expectancies, and Social Motivations).
