	abstract = {Introduction The longitudinal {ITC} Scotland/U.K. survey was used to investigate adult smokers’ support for smoke-free legislation and whether this support was associated with higher quit intentions at follow-up, either directly or indirectly, via the mediation of perceived social unacceptability of smoking.
